{
  "help": "Usage: privacy-pools [options] [command]\n\nPrivacy Pools: a compliant way to transact privately on Ethereum\n\nOptions:\n  -V, --version          output the version number\n  -c, --chain <name>     Target chain (mainnet, arbitrum, optimism, ...)\n  -j, --json             Machine-readable JSON output on stdout. After the\n                         command name, pass --json <fields> or --json=<fields>\n                         to select top-level fields.\n  -o, --output <format>  Output format: table (default), csv, json, yaml, wide,\n                         name (choices: \"table\", \"csv\", \"json\", \"yaml\", \"wide\",\n                         \"name\")\n  -y, --yes              Skip confirmation prompts\n  --web                  Open the primary explorer or portal link in your\n                         browser when available\n  --help-brief           Show condensed command help (default)\n  --help-full            Show full command help with examples, safety notes, and\n                         JSON fields\n  -r, --rpc-url <url>    Override RPC URL\n  --template <template>  Render structured output through a lightweight\n                         Mustache-style template with {{path.to.value}}\n                         placeholders and {{#items}}...{{/items}} list iteration\n  --agent                Machine-friendly mode (alias for --json --yes --quiet)\n  -q, --quiet            Suppress human-oriented stderr output\n  -v, --verbose          Enable verbose/debug output (-v info, -vv debug, -vvv\n                         trace)\n  --no-progress          Suppress spinners/progress indicators (useful in CI)\n  --no-header            Suppress header rows in CSV and wide/tabular table\n                         output\n  --no-banner            Disable welcome banner output\n  --no-color             Disable colored output (also respects NO_COLOR env var)\n  --timeout <seconds>    Network/transaction timeout in seconds (default: 30)\n  --jmes <expression>    Filter JSON output with a JMESPath expression (implies\n                         --json)\n  --jq <expression>      Compatibility alias for --jmes (JMESPath, not jq\n                         syntax)\n  --profile <name>       Use a named profile (separate wallet identity and\n                         config)\n  -h, --help             display help for command\n\nCommands:\n  init                   Create, load, or finish setting up your Privacy Pools\n                         account\n  upgrade                Check for CLI updates\n  config                 View and manage CLI configuration\n  flow                   Deposit and privately withdraw in one guided workflow\n  simulate               Preview deposit, withdraw, and ragequit without\n                         submitting\n  pools                  Browse available pools\n  deposit                Deposit ETH or ERC-20 tokens into a pool\n  accounts               View balances, approval status, and Pool Accounts\n  migrate                Check migration status for legacy Pool Accounts\n  withdraw               Withdraw privately from a pool\n  recipients|recents     Manage remembered withdrawal recipients\n  ragequit               Recover funds publicly to your deposit address\n  broadcast              Broadcast a signed envelope or relayer request built\n                         elsewhere\n  history                View your deposit and withdrawal history\n  sync                   Sync account state with the latest onchain data\n  tx-status              Check async transaction submission status\n  status                 Check account setup and network status\n  activity               View recent deposits and withdrawals across pools\n  protocol-stats         View aggregate network statistics\n  pool-stats             View statistics for one pool\n  stats                  Deprecated compatibility alias for protocol-stats and\n                         pool-stats\n  guide                  Learn key concepts, workflows, and troubleshooting\n  capabilities           Describe CLI capabilities for agents\n  describe               Describe a command's flags, args, and output schema\n  completion             Generate or install shell tab completion\n  help                   display help for command\n\nCommon workflows:\n  Easy path         privacy-pools flow start 0.1 ETH --to <address>\n  Manual path       privacy-pools deposit 0.1 ETH\n  Watch review      privacy-pools accounts --chain mainnet --pending-only\n  Withdraw          privacy-pools withdraw --all ETH --to <address>\n\n  Get started:      privacy-pools init\n  Full guide:       privacy-pools guide\n  Command help:     privacy-pools <command> --help\n  Agent discovery:  privacy-pools capabilities\n  Agent skill:      skills/privacy-pools-cli/SKILL.md",
